  <anchor role="helpid" condition="testSpecificationViewContextId" xml:id="using-filters-in-the-ite.testSpecificationViewContextId" xreflabel="Test Case Browser"/>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="objectMapEditorContextId" xml:id="using-filters-in-the-ite.objectMapEditorContextId" xreflabel="Object Mapping"/>
  <anchor role="helpid" condition="guidancerComponentNameBrowserContextId" xml:id="using-filters-in-the-ite.guidancerComponentNameBrowserContextId" xreflabel="Component Name Browser"/>
  <section xml:id="text-filters">
    <title>Text filters</title>
    <para>
      The Test Case Browser, the Test Suite Browser, the Component
      Names Browser and the Object Mapping Editor (in the tree view)
      all contain a filter area at the top. You can enter a filter
      text into this area to show matches to the text in the browser
      or editor. Use star (*) as a wildcard.
    </para>
    <para>
      In the Test Case Browser, the Component Names Browser and the
      Test Suite Browser, the names of the items in the browser are
      considered for the filter.
    </para>
    <para>
      In the Object Mapping Editor, the names and
      <emphasis>types</emphasis> of the components are considered
      for the filter.
    </para>
  </section>
</section>